---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="apt repository — goldfang" description="personal apt repository for goldfang's tools">
  <h1>apt repository</h1>

  <div class="prose">
    <p>
      a personal <code>apt</code> repository hosting my own tools. add it once,
      install them anywhere. hosted on github pages — no servers, no tailscale.
    </p>

    <h2>available packages</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>backup-util</h3>
      <p>backup utility with scheduling and restore.</p>
      <span class="tag tag-apt">python</span>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>howler</h3>
      <p>log aggregation and search. cli, tui, and gui frontends.</p>
      <span class="tag tag-apt">rust</span>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>luna-rs</h3>
      <p>TI-Nspire file transfer tool.</p>
      <span class="tag tag-apt">rust</span>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>lupine</h3>
      <p>fast, minimal file sync tool.</p>
      <span class="tag tag-apt">electron</span>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>mcp-sysd</h3>
      <p>systemd integration for MCP — manage services through natural language.</p>
      <span class="tag tag-apt">rust</span>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>russtly</h3>
      <p>native podcast client.</p>
      <span class="tag tag-apt">rust</span>
    </div>

    <h2>setup (ubuntu/debian)</h2>

    <p>1. add the signing key:</p>
    <pre><code>curl -fsSL https://realgoldfang.github.io/apt/pubkey.gpg | sudo gpg --dearmor -o /etc/apt/keyrings/goldfang.gpg</code></pre>

    <p>2. add the repository:</p>
    <pre><code>echo "deb [signed-by=/etc/apt/keyrings/goldfang.gpg] https://realgoldfang.github.io/apt stable main" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/goldfang.list</code></pre>

    <p>3. install packages:</p>
    <pre><code>sudo apt update && sudo apt install mcp-sysd</code></pre>

    <h2>supported distributions</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><code>noble</code> — Ubuntu 24.04 (amd64, arm64)</li>
      <li><code>plucky</code> — Ubuntu 26.04 (amd64, arm64)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>how it works</h2>
    <p>
      packages are built from source via github actions on each release tag.
      aptly manages the repo metadata and signing. the resulting static tree
      is published to github pages — no server-side processing, no aptly daemon.
    </p>

    <h2>troubleshooting</h2>
    <p>
      if you get a <code>BADSIG</code> error, re-download the signing key. keys
      rotate annually or on compromise — check this page for the latest
      instructions.
    </p>
  </div>
</Base>

<style>
  pre { font-size: 0.85rem; }
  pre code { word-break: break-all; white-space: pre-wrap; }
</style>
